President Trump and French President Macron held a joint press conference at the White House. They discussed a range of topics including the Iran nuclear deal, the fight against ISIS, trade relations, and the situation in Syria. President Macron expressed his willingness to work on a new deal with Iran that would address concerns about nuclear activity, ballistic activity, and regional influence. President Trump reiterated his desire to see complete denuclearization of North Korea and emphasized the need for other countries, particularly wealthy Middle Eastern nations, to contribute more to regional security efforts. The two leaders also discussed the ongoing trade dispute and the need for fair and reciprocal trade policies. Overall, the press conference highlighted the areas of agreement and disagreement between the two leaders, but also emphasized their commitment to maintaining a strong and productive relationship.